This paper is about a latent variable model for predicting the relationship between a pair of text sequences. The focus is on natural language inference and paraphrase identification, which are both subfields of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of semantic constraints, which are relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
